**SELLER OFFERING BUYERS AGENT 2K BONUS AT CLOSING***

Brand new roof installed 11/7/23, water heater installed 1/17/24, Eco saver pool equipment installed 6 months ago!!

Welcome to your dream home in the desirable Covington Park Community of Apollo Beach! 
This stunning residence boasts 4 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, very sizable 2 car garage, a lake view, and beautiful swimming pool. As you step inside, you'll immediately notice the high ceilings and open floor plan, creating an inviting and airy atmosphere throughout. The interior is flooded with natural light, enhancing the overall warmth and elegance of the space. The heart of this home lies in the beautifully designed kitchen, equipped with stainless steel appliances, sleek granite countertops and plenty of storage space. Whether you're preparing a gourmet meal or enjoying a quick breakfast, this culinary haven will inspire your inner chef. One of the standout features of this property the swimming pool overlooking the serene lake. New power saving pool system nestled within a screened-in patio. Imagine relaxing on a warm summer day, surrounded by the splendor and tranquility of your own private oasis. The fenced yard ensures privacy and security, allowing you to fully enjoy the outdoor living space while also offering a spectacular lake view right behind the home. Every aspect of this residence has been thoughtfully cared for, providing you with a move-in ready home. For added peace of mind, this home features a surround alarm surveillance system with cameras, ensuring the safety and security of your loved ones if you choose to keep it. All 4 bedrooms are very spacious and the primary suite offers a walk-in closet and an ensuite bathroom with a huge corner set dual sink vanity. A sitting area, walk-in shower, and garden tub. Covington Park now offers BRAND NEW amenities for its residents, including: a fitness/gym center, playgrounds, tennis courts, basketball court multiple swimming pools with Splash Pads! Major holiday events for the community. Elementary school is within the community, Middle and High Schools are within the community. You’ll be conveniently close to many shopping and dining restaurants of your choice. Jump right on to Hwy 41 N/S Bound or I-75, your choice! Approximately 22 miles from downtown Tampa. Welcome to your Eden!
**SERIOUS BUYERS - Seller is willing to listen to all offers.
